    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lean-beef-and-mushroom-chilli-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong></p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p><p>Slice <strong>half </strong>your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> into rounds and finely chop the rest</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lean-beef-and-mushroom-chilli-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>grated mushrooms </strong>with the <strong>diced onion</strong>,<strong> pepper </strong>and <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lean-beef-and-mushroom-chilli-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your <strong>mince</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>with your <strong>ground cumin </strong>and <strong>ground coriander </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lean-beef-and-mushroom-chilli-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>tomato beef stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lean-beef-and-mushroom-chilli-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince is browned, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>and <strong>tomato beef stock </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and <strong>salt </strong>and cook for a further 5-6 min or until the sauce has thickened and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>mince & white cup mushroom chilli</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lean-beef-and-mushroom-chilli-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>lighter cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lean-beef-and-mushroom-chilli-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>mince & white cup mushroom chilli </strong>with the <strong>brown rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>grated cheese </strong>and <strong>sliced chillies </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Finish with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
